<img width="107" height="107" src="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Court-107x107.jpg?resize=107%2C107&#038;ssl=1" alt="Teenager docked for alleged phone theft in examination hall" align="left" style="margin: 0 20px 20px 0;max-width:100%" data-recalc-dims="1" /> <img class="aligncenter wp-image-1290715 size-full" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/court-560x416.jpg?w=560&#038;ssl=1" alt="Court: Man gets reward, sentence without bail for beating mother" style="margin:10px auto;max-width:560px;max-width:100%" data-recalc-dims="1"> A teenager, Alade Mujeed, was on Monday arraigned in an Ile-Ife Magistrates’ Court in Osun for allegedly stealing an Infinix Hot5 mobile phone worth N35,000 in an examination hall. The 18-year-old is standing trial on a two-count charge of entering and stealing. The Prosecutor, Insp Sunday Osanyintuyi, told the court that the defendant committed the offence on Sept. 13 at about 12:00 p.m. at Oduduwa College Examination Hall, Ile-Ife. Osanyintuyi said that the defendant entered the examination hall with the intent to commit a felony therein. He added that the defendant opened the bag of one Giwa Samuel and stole the phone. According to him, the offence contravenes Sections 383, 390(9) and 413 of the Criminal Code of Osun, 2002. The defendant, however, pleaded not guilty to the charge. The Defence Counsel, Mr Kehinde Adegbite, prayed the court to grant bail to his client in the most liberal terms. The counsel pledged that his client would not jump bail, but would provide substantial sureties. The Magistrate, Joseph Owolawi, granted bail to the defendant in the sum of N100,000 with one surety in like sum. Owolawi added that the surety must swear to an affidavit of means and reside within the court’s jurisdiction. He said the surety’s address must be verified in addition to providing three recent passport photographs. The magistrate adjourned the case till Jan. 7, 2020, for hearing. Vanguard The post Teenager docked for alleged phone theft in examination hall appeared first on Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard Tribune Online Police arraign 2 men in court for alleged fraud THE police, on Friday, arraigned Oladimeji Timothy, 20, and Shola Emmanuel, 23 before an Ile-Ife Magistratesâ€™ Court in Osun for alleged fraud. The prosecutor, Insp Sunday Osanyintuyi, told the court that the defendants committed the offence sometimes in August… June 14, 2019 In "News" The police, on Friday, arraigned Oladimeji Timothy, 20, and Shola Emmanuel, 23 before an Ile-Ife Magistratesâ€™ Court in Osun for alleged fraud. The prosecutor, Insp Sunday Osanyintuyi, told the court that the defendants committed the offence sometimes in August, 2018 and June, 2019 around 12 p.m. at Oduduwa University, Ile-Ife.… June 14, 2019 In "News" An Ile-Ife Magistratesâ€™ Court in Osun on Friday remanded a 32-year-old man, Adewale Odunlade, in prison custody over alleged contempt of court. The Prosecutor, Insp Sunday Osanyintuyi, told the court that the accused committed the offence on April 18 at about 9:00 am at a Chief Magistratesâ€™ Court in Ile-Ife.… June 7, 2019 In "News"